    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How to Recognize Justice</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kenneth L Houghton letter on Harvey Araton's May 16 article holds New York Knicks' Latrell Sprewell should have banned permanently from NBA years ago; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>The next time Harvey Araton or another columnist praises the Knicks in general or Latrell Sprewell in particular, will you take to the editorial page to point out that Sprewell should have been banned permanently from the N.B.A. years ago.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>The next time Harvey Araton or another columnist praises the Knicks in general or Latrell Sprewell in particular, will you take to the editorial page to point out that Sprewell should have been banned permanently from the N.B.A. years ago.</p>
        <p>Myles Brand and the rest of us ''toadies'' -- the people who watch Knight's players graduate and be successful in life (generally without a notable N.B.A. career) -- know the difference between justice and pandering. It's a pity Araton and The Times do not.</p>
        <p>KENNETH  L. HOUGHTON  Maplewood, N.J.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
